                                    "bbox": [
                                        1282,
                                        1930,
                                        2272,
                                        2620
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "To validate the accuracy of the camera parameters, we compared our method with conventional methods that estimate both rotation and distortion. Following [53], we evaluated the mean absolute error and reprojection error (REPE). Our method achieved the lowest mean absolute angle error and REPE of the methods listed in Table 7. The pan- angle errors in our method using HRNet- W32 for the VP estimator are substantially smaller than those of Lochman et al.'s method [32] by "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1282,
                                        1930,
                                        2272,
                                        2620
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "20.16^{\\circ}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1282,
                                        1930,
                                        2272,
                                        2620
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " on the SL- MH test set. Our method achieved "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1282,
                                        1930,
                                        2272,
                                        2620
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "3.15^{\\circ}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1282,
                                        1930,
                                        2272,
                                        2620
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " and "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1282,
                                        1930,
                                        2272,
                                        2620
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "3.00^{\\circ}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1282,
                                        1930,
                                        2272,
                                        2620
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " errors for the tilt and roll angles, respectively, outperforming the other methods. We evaluated our method using HRNet- W48 (a larger backbone) and obtained a slight RMSE improvement of 0.16 pixels with respect to the RMSE obtained using HRNet- W32."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
